        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/wsgi.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/asgi.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/wsgi.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/asgi.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/utils/deprecation.py\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler.load_middleware\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler.get_response\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler.get_response_async\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler._get_response\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler._get_response_async\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/wsgi.py\", \"symbol\": \"WSGIHandler\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/asgi.py\", \"symbol\": \"ASGIHandler\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/utils/deprecation.py\", \"symbol\": \"MiddlewareMixin\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/utils/deprecation.py\", \"symbol\": \"MiddlewareMixin.__call__\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/utils/deprecation.py\", \"symbol\": \"MiddlewareMixin.__acall__\"}\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/wsgi.py\", \"symbol\": \"WSGIHandler.__call__\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler.get_response\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/core/handlers/base.py\", \"symbol\": \"BaseHandler._get_response\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Django's middleware processing is implemented primarily in django/core/handlers/base.py. The BaseHandler.load_middleware() method (line 27-104) reads the settings.MIDDLEWARE configuration and builds the middleware stack in REVERSED order (line 41). Each middleware class is imported and instantiated with the handler as a parameter (lines 42-63), creating a nested chain of callables.\\n\\nThe middleware stack construction works by wrapping: the innermost handler is the view resolution logic (_get_response/_get_response_async), and each middleware wraps around it. When settings.MIDDLEWARE is reversed and iterated, the last middleware in the config becomes the outermost layer, creating proper request/response flow.\\n\\nThe MiddlewareMixin class (django/utils/deprecation.py, lines 275-331) provides the interface that Django middlewares implement. The __call__ method (lines 302-312) handles process_request, then delegates to get_response (which calls the next handler), then process_response. For async, __acall__ (lines 314-331) handles the same pattern with async/await.\\n\\nThe call order differs from WSGI stacking:\\n- WSGI middleware stacks vertically where each middleware wraps the next, all request processing on entry, all response processing on exit\\n- Django separates process_request (called in forward order during request phase) and process_response (called in reverse order during response phase)\\n- The BaseHandler implements process_view (lines 186-191) and process_template_response (lines 211-220) hooks that are called at specific points in the view execution pipeline\\n- Exception middleware (process_exception) is processed separately (lines 358-367)\\n\\nThe WSGI entry point (django/core/wsgi.py) and ASGI entry point (django/core/asgi.py) both create handler instances that call load_middleware(). WSGIHandler (django/core/handlers/wsgi.py, line 113) calls load_middleware() synchronously, while ASGIHandler (django/core/handlers/asgi.py, line 143) calls load_middleware(is_async=True) to adapt middleware for async execution.\\n\\nWhen processing a request:\\n1. WSGI/ASGI handler receives the request\\n2. Handler.get_response() or get_response_async() is called with the request\\n3. The _middleware_chain (the outermost middleware wrapper) is invoked\\n4. Each middleware's process_request is called in forward order\\n5. The view is executed\\n6. Each middleware's process_response is called in reverse order\\n7. The response is returned\\n\\nThis design allows Django middlewares to have fine-grained control over both request and response phases while maintaining the familiar onion/decorator pattern seen in traditional WSGI middleware.\"\n}\n",
